Test: I don’t want to sleep yet.
I don’t want to sleep yet.
I don’t want to sleep yet.
I don’t want to sleep yet.
I’m tired… but it’s too early.
I don’t want to sleep yet.
I don’t want to sleep yet.
It’s hard, but I need to at least try...
I feel… off. Maybe just tired.
Sleep didn’t help. I just need to start moving.
Feels like this body isn’t mine.
Wish I could just get some real sleep.
Can’t get it out of my head.
Please, just make it all stop.
Got a bit more energy after the run.
It was hard, but I’m not giving up.
Feels like I’m not in shape anymore.
People say “Stay strong”. So you hang in there too, huh.
“Stay strong”? What the hell am I supposed to stay strong for?
Feels like we’re both falling apart.
Feels like we’re both falling apart.
I don’t feel anything. Not hunger. Not taste.
I don’t feel anything. Not hunger. Not taste.
Is this supposed to be a joke?
I can’t get it out of my head...
Well, I did everything I could.
“Stay strong”? What does that even mean?!
What does it say? I can’t tell.
I remember us singing in the kitchen, the four of us…
We even talked about playing on a stage someday...
Haven’t played in a while. Should probably tune it sometime.
We used to drag it to the lake: campfire, wet sand, strings smelling of smoke.
Now it’s just deadlines and doctor’s visits. The fires live in photos.
I can’t even remember where A minor goes.
My fingers shake, and my head’s full of test results.
The guitar’s in the corner. I’m not touching it. Not now.
Don’t even want to replace it. Let it stay off.
The strings ring too loud. It’s irritating.
I want it to sound again. But I can’t.
It’s dusty. Feels like it’s not mine anymore.
The guitar doesn’t recognize me. And I don’t recognize it.
Noise in my head drowns everything.
Too heavy. Even my eyes slide past it.
I suddenly decided I was going to paint…
I bought brushes, canvases, and even brought an easel from the village...
And never finished a single one.
Every time I’d say, “I’ll start painting as soon as I wrap up this project”…
The canvases just sit there. Waiting, same as me.
One day I picked up a brush and just stared at the canvas…
No image, no spark. Only a low hum in my head…
Set the brush down. Didn’t even pour out the water.
These canvases weigh on me like open loops…
What was I even trying to say with them?
Shoved the whole stack into a corner. Kept bumping into it, got angry…
Wanted to throw it all out, but my hand wouldn’t move…
They just get in the way. Like so much else.
Too much emptiness. Inside me, on the canvas…
Too late to finish anything now…
No one’s going to see it anyway.
I was always dragging books home from sales — for “inspiration”…
Sometimes I’d read at night, mark passages, scribble in the margins…
I should at least finish one someday.
The bookmark’s still on the same page...
What was it even about? I forgot.
The books stare at me. Judging.
My brain refuses to absorb the text.
I can’t hold a single thought.
Just meaningless words, wrapped in paper.
What could they tell me that I’m not already feeling?
Maybe I should throw them out. Make space.
It all presses down like someone else’s expectations...
I don’t think I can even read the titles anymore.
Finishing them won’t make me stronger.
The books are gone. Just empty rectangles now.
I wanted to learn knitting, but I never had the patience.
Someday I’ll make a scarf. Maybe for me. Maybe for someone else.
The colors feel so warm. Nice to touch.
There’s always something else. No time for yarn.
I started a couple times. Then gave up.
They tangle just like my thoughts.
The hook’s broken. I didn’t even notice when.
I can’t focus. Every stitch feels like a task.
I’m not even angry. Just watching it fade away...
Why is it so hard to let go of useless things?
Fine motor skills are the enemy now.
Everything in this basket is a frozen “what never was.”
I love the morning light. Everything feels possible.
Even the birds sound like they’re whispering.
It’s sunny… but strange. Like it’s on delay.
Today was supposed to be a good day. Maybe.
People move forward. I feel like I’m not allowed.
The world outside looks out of focus.
Rain noise makes it hard to think.
Puddles reflect the ceiling. Can’t even see the sky.
Everything’s gone gray. Even the trees.
Just water and glass. That’s all.
The world’s losing it. And I’m just… left behind.
I can’t see anything. Not even myself in the reflection.
